Mulholland Drive and Cahuenga Pass.

473
00:37:26,040 --> 00:37:29,555
- We'll discuss your end ofthe bargain.
- What are you talking about?

474
00:37:29,640 --> 00:37:32,200
- You gotta kill my mother.
- Kill your mother?!

475
00:37:32,280 --> 00:37:34,669
7.30, Cahuenga Pass. Crisscross.

476
00:37:34,760 --> 00:37:36,751
- Owen, I...
- (Owen hangs up)

477
00:37:37,120 --> 00:37:39,031
Crisscross... Criss...

478
00:37:39,120 --> 00:37:43,033
Holy shit. He did it.
He did it! The little bastard did it!

479
00:37:43,120 --> 00:37:46,954
He killed my wi... No, he didn't do it.
He couldn't poss... No, he didn't do it.

480
00:37:47,040 --> 00:37:49,554
I'll call her up, call her up on the phone.

481
00:37:49,640 --> 00:37:52,996
She'll answer the phone,
I'll hang up, and she won't be dead.

482
00:37:53,080 --> 00:37:55,071
That's it and that's all.

483
00:37:59,040 --> 00:38:01,031
(phone rings)

484
00:38:05,080 --> 00:38:09,710
Come on, come on, Margaret. Answer
the phone. Answer the phone, Margaret.

485
00:38:10,120 --> 00:38:13,032
Why the hell isn't she
answering the phone?

486
00:38:13,120 --> 00:38:16,999
Because she's dead. That's why
she's not answering the phone.

487
00:38:17,080 --> 00:38:19,833
You don't answer the phone
when you're dead!

488
00:38:21,720 --> 00:38:24,871
They're gonna think I did it.
They're gonna think that I did it!

489
00:38:24,960 --> 00:38:28,077
Why would they think that I did it?
Because I hate her guts!

490
00:38:28,160 --> 00:38:30,913
That's why they'll think
that I did it. My God...

491
00:38:31,840 --> 00:38:33,432
I have no alibi.

492
00:38:33,520 --> 00:38:36,512
Lester! I was with you yesterday! Lester!

493
00:38:40,480 --> 00:38:44,758
- I was with you yesterday, right, Lester?
- Right. And now I'm with Ms Gladstone.

494
00:38:45,120 --> 00:38:47,395
I left the club at one.
I couldn't have done it!

495
00:38:47,480 --> 00:38:51,109
That's right. You couldn't have done it.
Close the door on your way out.

496
00:38:51,200 --> 00:38:55,273
I couldn't have gone to Hawaii and back
in that time. So what am I worried about?

497
00:38:55,360 --> 00:38:59,592
That's what I'd like to know. Hawaii
and back? No way, man. You're cool.

498
00:38:59,680 --> 00:39:04,549
Well... Now, if he left the club at one,
he could catch the three o'clock flight.

499
00:39:04,640 --> 00:39:07,916
You could be in Hawaii by five,
given the three-hour time change.

500
00:39:08,000 --> 00:39:10,798
- She's got a point.
- You could spend four hours there...

501
00:39:10,880 --> 00:39:13,474
.. and still catch the last flight out by ten.

502
00:39:13,560 --> 00:39:16,916
- That's true.
- You'd arrive at LAX by 6am.

503
00:39:17,000 --> 00:39:21,039
An hour on the freeway...
You'd be home by seven.

504
00:39:21,120 --> 00:39:24,396
Whatever it is, you're fuckin' guilty, man.

505
00:39:24,480 --> 00:39:26,994
Meet Senior Flight Supervisor Gladstone.

506
00:39:27,080 --> 00:39:30,629
Hi. Pleased to meet you. Listen,
I've got a flight schedule in here.

507
00:39:30,720 --> 00:39:33,188
- I was on a rock!
- A rock?

508
00:39:33,280 --> 00:39:36,750
They're gonna think I did it!
I'm all motive and no alibi!

509
00:39:36,840 --> 00:39:38,910
I have no alibi! Motives are no problem.

510
00:39:39,000 --> 00:39:41,514
I'm up to my ass in motives.
I'm majoring in motives.

511
00:39:41,600 --> 00:39:45,878
Alibi, nowhere near my neighbourhood.
But motives: whooo-ooh!

512
00:39:45,960 --> 00:39:49,953
- I gotta go! Can I borrow your car?
- Sure, man. The keys are on the table...

513
00:39:50,040 --> 00:39:52,679
.. next to the door. Goodbye.

514
00:39:53,400 --> 00:39:55,516
I gotta find Beth.

515
00:39:56,800 --> 00:39:59,678
What am I doing?
What the hell am I doing?!

516
00:39:59,760 --> 00:40:02,513
She's not dead.
I'm crazy. I'm a crazy man.

517
00:40:02,600 --> 00:40:05,239
She is not dead. He didn't kill her.

518
00:40:06,440 --> 00:40:10,433
News from Hawaii: Novelist Margaret
Donner is missing and presumed dead.

519
00:40:11,520 --> 00:40:14,193
- According to the police...
- Holy Christ!

520
00:40:14,280 --> 00:40:16,589
I'm not crazy! She's presumed!

521
00:40:16,680 --> 00:40:20,912
She was last seen boarding a boat
to Maui. She disappeared along route.

522
00:40:21,000 --> 00:40:24,436
- A search is on for the body.
- Margaret is dead! Poor Margaret!

523
00:40:24,520 --> 00:40:27,796
She is the renowned author
of the best-selling novel "Hot Fire".

524
00:40:27,880 --> 00:40:31,077
That slut! She is a slut! Slut!

525
00:40:31,160 --> 00:40:33,355
Foul play has not been ruled out.

526
00:40:34,200 --> 00:40:35,474
I'm gonna fry!

527
00:40:35,560 --> 00:40:37,551
( didgeridoo playing)

528
00:40:38,920 --> 00:40:40,319
(door shuts)

529
00:40:40,840 --> 00:40:42,831
I'm in really deep shit, Beth.

530
00:40:42,920 --> 00:40:45,912
Ah. Look who's decided
to breeze back into my life.

531
00:40:46,360 --> 00:40:48,828
- I gotta talk to you.
- You have to talk to me?

532
00:40:48,920 --> 00:40:53,072
You don't return my calls or get in touch.
But hey, you need something from me?

533
00:40:54,560 --> 00:40:56,551
Make yourself at home. Have a seat.

534
00:40:56,640 --> 00:40:58,949
Can I offer you something? A cool drink?

535
00:40:59,040 --> 00:41:01,554
Would you listen to me?
I'm in a lot of trouble!

536
00:41:01,640 --> 00:41:03,870
- I'm on the edge of my seat.
- It's Margaret.

537
00:41:03,960 --> 00:41:05,871
Don't tell me! She's come back.

538
00:41:05,960 --> 00:41:08,349
- She's...
- Pregnant, put on weight...

539
00:41:08,440 --> 00:41:10,635
She's dead!

540
00:41:10,720 --> 00:41:12,233
Oh, God.

541
00:41:12,320 --> 00:41:14,914
- It's awful.
- Larry, I'm sorry.

542
00:41:16,520 --> 00:41:19,353
- Did she suffer?
- He said she didn't feel a thing.

543
00:41:19,440 --> 00:41:20,873
- Her doctor?
- Her killer.

544
00:41:20,960 --> 00:41:24,430
- She was killed?!
- She's dead. It works that way.

545
00:41:24,520 --> 00:41:27,273
Wait! Did the police find a clue
or have a motive or...

546
00:41:27,360 --> 00:41:31,751
If there was a motive, the fat little bastard
never would've killed her! Don't you see?

547
00:41:31,840 --> 00:41:34,149
Eliminate the motive, establish an alibi.

548
00:41:34,520 --> 00:41:37,876
- Just like I told him!
- Just like you told him?!

549
00:41:37,960 --> 00:41:41,555
- We were speaking hypothetically.
- Larry Donner! Did...

550
00:41:42,120 --> 00:41:45,476
- Did you pay a man to kill your wife?
- No! He just did it.

551
00:41:45,560 --> 00:41:48,996
- Oh, my God!
- Hey, look. I told a guy something...

552
00:41:49,080 --> 00:41:50,991
.. and he took it the wrong way.

553
00:41:51,080 --> 00:41:53,469
What, uh... What did you say to him?

554
00:41:53,560 --> 00:41:56,757
- "Don't kill my wife", wink, wink?
- I don't like your tone.

555
00:41:56,840 --> 00:41:59,638
- Oh, God. You better leave.
- I got noplace else to go.

556
00:41:59,720 --> 00:42:03,474
- My head is spinning.
- Oh, and my head isn't creamed corn?

557
00:42:03,560 --> 00:42:07,997
You announced that you may or may not
have inadvertently murdered someone.

558
00:42:08,080 --> 00:42:09,069
Mm-hm.

559
00:42:09,160 --> 00:42:13,199
This puts me in a highly distracted
state of mind. I am nauseous.

560
00:42:13,280 --> 00:42:18,274
Great! Margaret is dead, I have no alibi,
and you're mad that I upset your stomach.

561
00:42:18,360 --> 00:42:22,478
Well, excuse me. I'll just go
so the police can start their manhunt!

562
00:42:23,560 --> 00:42:26,154
One little murder and I'm Jack the Ripper!

563
00:42:28,920 --> 00:42:31,718
Jeez, you think you know somebody.

564
00:42:43,160 --> 00:42:44,593
Cahuenga Pass.

565
00:42:44,680 --> 00:42:46,955
(Larry's voice)
Leave a snappy message. Bye.

566
00:42:47,040 --> 00:42:49,235
Larry, it's Beth. Um...

567
00:42:50,240 --> 00:42:54,711
Call me at home right now, OK?
As soon as you get in. I'm very confused.

568
00:42:54,800 --> 00:42:59,590
You... came in with just...
murder and Margaret, and I just...

569
00:43:00,320 --> 00:43:03,153
Call me... now. Thank you.

570
00:43:09,280 --> 00:43:11,635
- Larry!
- Get in the car, Owen.

571
00:43:11,720 --> 00:43:14,359
- This isn't your car.
- I borrowed it. Get in!

572
00:43:14,440 --> 00:43:17,830
I thought you might like to have this.
It belonged to Margaret.

573
00:43:17,920 --> 00:43:20,115
Get in the car. Get in the car!

574
00:43:23,560 --> 00:43:25,949
Look what you did. You killed my wife!

575
00:43:26,040 --> 00:43:28,031
No, I didn't. Yes, I did.

576
00:43:28,720 --> 00:43:31,951
You're sick, Owen. You need care.
I am taking you to the police.

577
00:43:32,040 --> 00:43:34,429
Did you know Hawaii
was a series of islands...

578
00:43:34,520 --> 00:43:37,990
.. that was all spit up by the same
volcano? I never knew that.

579
00:43:38,080 --> 00:43:41,595
You killed somebody!
You're a murderer! You took a life!

580
00:43:41,680 --> 00:43:45,878
You're right. I'm no good.
How could I do that? I'm a sick, sick per...

581
00:43:45,960 --> 00:43:48,235
Cows!

582
00:43:48,320 --> 00:43:51,676
- Why did you kill my wife?!
- I thought you wanted me to.

583
00:43:51,760 --> 00:43:56,038
You said you wished she was dead.
I told you I wished my momma was dead.

584
00:43:56,120 --> 00:43:58,680
I kill your wife, you kill my momma.
That's fair.

585
00:43:58,760 --> 00:44:00,955
I am not killing your mother.

586
00:44:01,040 --> 00:44:04,794
- You have to turn yourself in.
- No. It was part of our plan.

587
00:44:04,880 --> 00:44:08,555
What plan?!
There was no plan, you moron!

588
00:44:09,120 --> 00:44:11,998
You killed a person and
I'm takin' you to the police!

589
00:44:12,080 --> 00:44:16,073
I'll just tell 'em that you did it.
You got the motive.

590
00:44:16,760 --> 00:44:18,955
- You're gonna tell them the truth.
- Huh?

591
00:44:19,040 --> 00:44:22,919
You're gonna tell the police the truth
or I'll kill us both, I swear!

592
00:44:23,600 --> 00:44:26,353
- I didn't do this only for me.
- Say goodbye, Owen.

593
00:44:26,440 --> 00:44:29,432
Larry... Larry, slow down.
You're goin' a tad fast.

594
00:44:30,320 --> 00:44:33,118
Please slow down, Larry!
I don't like goin' fast!

595
00:44:33,200 --> 00:44:36,078
- Are you gonna tell 'em you did it?
- Please slow down!

596
00:44:36,280 --> 00:44:37,872
Huh?

597
00:44:38,560 --> 00:44:40,869
- Yeah. I'll do it.
- OK.

598
00:44:41,800 --> 00:44:43,597
- Please stop the car!
- I can't!

599
00:44:43,680 --> 00:44:45,750
- Stop the car!
- There's no brakes!

600
00:44:45,840 --> 00:44:49,196
- What?! Watch out for that car!
- (car horn)

601
00:44:49,280 --> 00:44:51,953
- Oh. You're a good driver, Larry.
- Just shut up!

602
00:45:06,880 --> 00:45:08,279
Larry! Larry!

603
00:45:12,720 --> 00:45:15,632
Larry, you're originally
from the East, aren't you?

604
00:45:16,120 --> 00:45:19,237
- Owen!
- A man on our block was from the East.

605
00:45:19,320 --> 00:45:21,550
Mr Brockman.
He was in the button business.

606
00:45:21,640 --> 00:45:23,790
- Is that right?
- Yeah. This is good!

607
00:45:23,880 --> 00:45:25,871
It's like the Flintstones car wash.

608
00:45:39,080 --> 00:45:41,753
Larry! Ooh, I can't look!

609
00:45:41,840 --> 00:45:44,115
(truck horn)

610
00:45:48,920 --> 00:45:50,114
Whoa!

611
00:46:13,160 --> 00:46:16,675
So are you telling me
you weren't driving that car?

612
00:46:16,760 --> 00:46:19,320
Look, man. It's like I told you.

613
00:46:19,720 --> 00:46:23,713
He borrowed the car yesterday morning
and I haven't seen him since.

614
00:46:24,560 --> 00:46:28,997
- Did he say where he was going?
- No. Mumbled about motives and alibis.

615
00:46:29,080 --> 00:46:30,957
Motives and alibis?

616
00:46:31,040 --> 00:46:35,511
He figured that since Margaret ruined his
life, you'd think he killed her or somethin'.

617
00:46:35,600 --> 00:46:38,034
- You don't think he did?
- No, I don't think so.

618
00:46:38,120 --> 00:46:41,669
Personally, if the bitch stole my book,
I'd kill her. But that's me.

619
00:46:41,760 --> 00:46:44,513
Larry? There's no way he coulda done it.

620
00:46:44,600 --> 00:46:46,909
What makes you say that?

621
00:46:47,000 --> 00:46:49,958
Because Larry never did...

622
00:46:50,040 --> 00:46:51,837
.. anything.

623
00:46:53,200 --> 00:46:56,875
OK. Here we go. Eggs a la Owen.

624
00:46:56,960 --> 00:46:59,713
(sighs) Owen, get it
through your thick head.

625
00:46:59,800 --> 00:47:02,473
I may be a lot of things,
but I am not a killer.

626
00:47:03,160 --> 00:47:05,469
You don't have to blow her brains out.

627
00:47:05,560 --> 00:47:08,632
Thank you! That takes
the pressure right off(!)

628
00:47:08,720 --> 00:47:11,553
She's old. She's got a bad ticker.

629
00:47:11,640 --> 00:47:14,552
All you gotta do is
jerk around a lot when you talk to her.

630
00:47:14,640 --> 00:47:17,438
- "Nice to meet you, Mrs Lift!"
- Would you stop it?

631
00:47:19,320 --> 00:47:23,279
Well, just meet her. Maybe she'd be
somebody you'd like to kill.

632
00:47:23,440 --> 00:47:26,273
(Momma) Owen! What the hell's
going on out there?!

633
00:47:26,360 --> 00:47:27,793
Nothing, Momma!

634
00:47:27,880 --> 00:47:32,032
- (whispers) We woke her up.
- Who are you talking to? Who's in there?

635
00:47:32,120 --> 00:47:33,712
- Nobody, Momma!
- (door bangs)

636
00:47:36,880 --> 00:47:38,871
Who's this?

637
00:47:40,200 --> 00:47:41,758
This is Cousin Paddy.

638
00:47:41,840 --> 00:47:45,833
He's gonna be stayin' with us for a while.
Isn't that nice?

639
00:47:46,680 --> 00:47:48,671
You don't have a Cousin Paddy!

640
00:47:51,000 --> 00:47:52,991
You lied to me!

641
00:47:53,760 --> 00:47:56,149
(Larry groans)

642
00:47:59,000 --> 00:48:01,798
- That's it. That's all.
- Larry... Larry.

643
00:48:03,200 --> 00:48:05,509
I'm sorry. She makes me so nervous.

644
00:48:05,600 --> 00:48:09,070
Come on. Go in there and sit down.
I'll get you some ice.

645
00:48:11,280 --> 00:48:13,840
So what do you think of her?

646
00:48:13,920 --> 00:48:16,354
I think she could relax a little bit.

647
00:48:17,400 --> 00:48:19,436
- Are you gonna do it?
- Owen...

648
00:48:19,520 --> 00:48:22,637
I'm not gonna kill your mother.
If you wanna do it, you do it.

649
00:48:22,720 --> 00:48:26,269
A guy kills my wife.
He can't even kill his own mother.

650
00:48:26,360 --> 00:48:28,794
- You wanna see my coin collection?
- No!

651
00:48:30,520 --> 00:48:32,511
I collect coins.

652
00:48:33,600 --> 00:48:36,956
- I got a dandy collection.
- I don't wanna see it, Owen.

653
00:48:38,280 --> 00:48:40,919
- But it's my collection.
- I don't care.

654
00:48:41,000 --> 00:48:43,639
Look, Owen. I'm just not in the mood. OK?

655
00:48:51,480 --> 00:48:53,550
Never showed it to anyone before.

656
00:48:56,360 --> 00:48:58,669
- All right, I'll look at it.
- No, it's OK.

657
00:48:58,760 --> 00:49:00,751
- Show it to me.
- No, you don't mean it.

658
00:49:00,840 --> 00:49:03,070
- Show me the damn coins!
- All right.

659
00:49:04,360 --> 00:49:06,351
This one is a nickel.

660
00:49:06,960 --> 00:49:09,235
This one also is a nickel.

661
00:49:10,480 --> 00:49:12,471
And here's a quarter.

662
00:49:13,440 --> 00:49:15,431
And another quarter.

663
00:49:17,480 --> 00:49:19,471
And a penny.

664
00:49:19,560 --> 00:49:22,438
See? Nickel, nickel,
quarter, quarter, penny.

665
00:49:22,520 --> 00:49:25,318
Are any of these coins worth anything?

666
00:49:25,880 --> 00:49:27,393
No.

667
00:49:27,480 --> 00:49:31,109
And here... is another nickel.

668
00:49:32,240 --> 00:49:35,277
- Why do you have them?
- What do you mean?

669
00:49:35,640 --> 00:49:40,031
The purpose of a coin collection is that
the coins are worth something, Owen.

670
00:49:40,120 --> 00:49:42,031
Oh, but they are.

671
00:49:42,120 --> 00:49:44,873
This one here I got in change...

672
00:49:44,960 --> 00:49:47,952
.. when my dad took me
to see Peter, Paul and Mary.

673
00:49:48,760 --> 00:49:53,197
And this one I got in change
when I bought a hot dog at the circus.

674
00:49:53,280 --> 00:49:57,068
My daddy let me keep the change.
He always let me keep the change.

675
00:49:57,240 --> 00:49:58,912
This one...

676
00:49:59,000 --> 00:50:00,752
.. is my favourite.

677
00:50:00,840 --> 00:50:04,958
This is Martin and Lewis
at the Hollywood Palladium.

678
00:50:05,440 --> 00:50:07,032
Look at that.

679
00:50:07,120 --> 00:50:10,396
See the way it shines on the little eagle?

680
00:50:12,640 --> 00:50:14,631
I loved my dad a lot.

681
00:50:17,120 --> 00:50:21,113
- So this whole collection is...
- Change my daddy let me keep.

682
00:50:21,920 --> 00:50:23,911
- What was his name?
- Ned.

683
00:50:24,000 --> 00:50:25,991
He used to call me his little Ned.

684
00:50:26,760 --> 00:50:29,194
That's why Momma named me Owen.

685
00:50:29,280 --> 00:50:31,271
I really miss him.

686
00:50:31,360 --> 00:50:34,557
- It's a real nice collection, Owen.
- Thank you, Larry.

687
00:50:34,640 --> 00:50:37,916
- Owen! Food!
- In a minute, Momma!

688
00:50:38,000 --> 00:50:42,198
Don't you "in a minute" me! Get off
your fat little ass or I'll break it for you!

689
00:50:42,280 --> 00:50:47,229
I want two soft-boiled eggs, white toast
and some of that grape jelly, goddammit!

690
00:50:47,320 --> 00:50:49,231
And don't burn the toast!

691
00:50:49,320 --> 00:50:50,799
- Kill her, Larry.
- I can't.

692
00:50:50,880 --> 00:50:55,192
You gotta kill her for me, Larry.
Don't you understand? Crisscross.

693
00:50:55,280 --> 00:50:59,592
Crisscross! You gotta do it, Larry!
If you don't, I will. I swear I will.

694
00:50:59,680 --> 00:51:01,989
Move it, fat boy!

695
00:51:02,080 --> 00:51:05,072
- That's it! I'm gonna choke her to death!
- No, Owen!

696
00:51:05,160 --> 00:51:07,230
I swear to God, I'm gonna kill her!

697
00:51:08,760 --> 00:51:10,591
- Calm down, Owen.
- Larry...

698
00:51:10,680 --> 00:51:13,831
It's gonna be OK. It's gonna be OK, Owen.

699
00:51:13,920 --> 00:51:15,911
I promise.

700
00:51:20,240 --> 00:51:22,117
Will you do it?

701
00:51:22,200 --> 00:51:24,077
Yeah. I'll do it.

702
00:51:24,200 --> 00:51:26,589
Larry, you're the best pal a guy ever had.

703
00:51:26,680 --> 00:51:28,910
Here. Look. I want you to have this.

704
00:51:29,000 --> 00:51:32,879
Look. Here. It's a souvenir from
the London Bridge gift shop in Arizona.

705
00:51:32,960 --> 00:51:38,193
Look. See? They brought this bridge over
from London, England, stone by stone.

706
00:51:38,280 --> 00:51:40,874
See the little bridge?
See the stones there?

707
00:51:40,960 --> 00:51:43,758
- Yeah, I see 'em.
- Here. You can have that.

708
00:51:48,240 --> 00:51:49,355
Crisscross.

709
00:51:50,880 --> 00:51:54,077
- When did you last see him?
- I can't remember. I told you.

710
00:51:55,120 --> 00:51:58,078
- The day after his wife disappeared?
- I didn't say that.

711
00:51:58,160 --> 00:52:02,631
- Miss Ryan, why are you protecting him?
- I'm not. I just don't think he killed her.

712
00:52:02,720 --> 00:52:05,188
Where do you think he is, Miss Ryan?

713
00:52:05,280 --> 00:52:07,111
I don't know!

714
00:52:08,160 --> 00:52:10,674
- He's in a lot of trouble.
- He didn't do it.

715
00:52:10,760 --> 00:52:13,479
Then who do you suppose did?

716
00:52:15,680 --> 00:52:18,558
- Somebody else.
- So you do think it was murder.

717
00:52:19,840 --> 00:52:22,912
- You know who killed her, don't you?
- No.

718
00:52:23,000 --> 00:52:25,992
- Yes, you do.
- I do not! He wouldn't tell me!

719
00:52:29,920 --> 00:52:33,469
Did Professor Donner
hire a man to kill his wife?

720
00:52:33,560 --> 00:52:36,552
No! He said... not really.

721
00:52:40,440 --> 00:52:44,956
And I heard him scream out
"I hate her! I wish she were dead!"

722
00:52:45,280 --> 00:52:48,716
Yeah, I heard him. He said
"I hate her. I wish she was dead. "

723
00:52:48,800 --> 00:52:50,597
That's what he said.

724
00:52:50,880 --> 00:52:53,872
"I hate her. I wish she was dead. "

725
00:52:54,800 --> 00:52:56,791
He called her a very bad name...

726
00:52:56,880 --> 00:52:59,997
.. and screamed "I hate her.
I wish she were dead. "

727
00:53:01,360 --> 00:53:03,351
It's a coffee-table book.

728
00:53:06,320 --> 00:53:08,231
(TV on)

729
00:53:10,480 --> 00:53:12,311
All right, Momma.

730
00:53:12,400 --> 00:53:14,709
Turn off the TV.

731
00:53:14,800 --> 00:53:16,472
OK.

732
00:53:18,280 --> 00:53:20,271
Goodbye, Momma.

733
00:53:25,160 --> 00:53:29,711
- She'll be sleepin' in a couple of minutes.
- I graduated from Yale.

734
00:53:30,640 --> 00:53:33,712
All right. Out you go.

735
00:53:34,120 --> 00:53:36,998
- Out? Out where?
- Out on the ledge. Go out on the roof...

736
00:53:37,080 --> 00:53:41,517
- No, no. I'm not going out on any ledge.
- You gotta make it look like a burglar.

737
00:53:41,600 --> 00:53:45,149
- You go in, you mess up things...
- No, Owen. This is going too far.

738
00:53:45,240 --> 00:53:46,719
- You want outta this?
- Yes.

739
00:53:46,800 --> 00:53:51,271
Then fulfil your end of the bargain. You go
in, stuff a pillow over her face and leave.

740
00:53:51,360 --> 00:53:54,716
You walk out that door.
You never have to see me again, OK?

741
00:53:54,800 --> 00:53:56,631
Oh, God!

742
00:53:59,000 --> 00:54:03,391
- OK. Out you go.
- Shit. I hate heights.

743
00:54:04,680 --> 00:54:05,635
Larry!

744
00:54:10,160 --> 00:54:12,151
- You all right? Move your hand.
- Why?

745
00:54:12,240 --> 00:54:13,878
Gotta close the window.

746
00:54:19,360 --> 00:54:21,828
And like this you kill an evening.

747
00:54:24,520 --> 00:54:26,909
Rats! Now I got Willard here.

748
00:54:28,680 --> 00:54:33,993
I'm bein' held captive by a little troll who
should be hanging off a rear-view mirror.

749
00:54:34,080 --> 00:54:36,071
I'm not doin' this.

750
00:54:38,760 --> 00:54:40,432
- Aargh!
- What are you doin'?

751
00:54:40,520 --> 00:54:43,432
I'm selling The Watchtower!
What do you think?!

752
00:54:43,520 --> 00:54:46,478
You got rats the size of Oldsmobiles here!

753
00:54:48,760 --> 00:54:50,830
Rats.

754
00:54:50,920 --> 00:54:54,435
OK, forget about the burglar stuff.
Just go through her door.

755
00:54:54,520 --> 00:54:59,275
It's less dramatic but I don't wanna
make you uncomfortable. Here, use this.

756
00:54:59,360 --> 00:55:02,272
- I really don't like you, Owen.
- OK, I gotta go.

757
00:55:02,360 --> 00:55:05,591
If I'm late for my lane,
they tack on an extra buck.

758
00:55:13,600 --> 00:55:15,591
Ugh. What a week.

759
00:55:43,000 --> 00:55:48,154
Mrs Lift, I know you don't want to hear
anything derogatory about your son.

760
00:55:48,240 --> 00:55:53,712
I understand that. Because he's not a bad
man, Mrs Lift. He's a nice man, actually.

761
00:55:53,800 --> 00:55:56,678
He is a lunatic. No, Mrs Lift, he is.

762
00:55:56,760 --> 00:55:58,955
He's a lunatic. And, um...

763
00:55:59,280 --> 00:56:03,273
I don't have to be here now, Mrs Lift.
I could be in Mexico, out of all of this.

764
00:56:03,360 --> 00:56:05,749
I'm only here to stop him fr...

765
00:56:07,640 --> 00:56:10,029
How do you say this, Mrs Lift?

766
00:56:10,720 --> 00:56:12,756
Listen to me, Mrs Lift.

767
00:56:13,120 --> 00:56:16,317
Your son... killed my wife.

768
00:56:17,040 --> 00:56:20,635
And now he wants me to kill you.

769
00:56:21,800 --> 00:56:23,995
(snores)

770
00:56:24,400 --> 00:56:26,789
- Mrs Lift?
- (snores)

771
00:56:29,840 --> 00:56:33,355
- I'm gonna go read the paper now and...
- (snoring continues)

772
00:56:33,440 --> 00:56:35,874
I'm just glad we had this chance to talk.

773
00:56:37,280 --> 00:56:39,111
(snores)

774
00:56:40,920 --> 00:56:44,959
I'm a fugitive. The little bastard
turned me into Richard Kimble.

775
00:56:45,040 --> 00:56:48,350
He shit and shoved me in it.
I gotta get outta here! I gotta go!

776
00:56:49,680 --> 00:56:53,195
Where am I running? Evidence.
Incriminating evidence!

777
00:56:57,680 --> 00:56:59,477
Nothing.

778
00:57:03,400 --> 00:57:05,391
Ha! A lei.

779
00:57:05,920 --> 00:57:07,911
Poha jelly.

780
00:57:08,640 --> 00:57:10,631
Not enough!

781
00:57:11,200 --> 00:57:14,317
Poha jelly, a lei and a doll.
I need some evidence.

782
00:57:14,400 --> 00:57:16,391
Aha! Bingo. The mother lode.

783
00:57:16,480 --> 00:57:19,199
A plane ticket!
A little careless, Owen, aren't we?

784
00:57:19,280 --> 00:57:21,475
Los Angeles, Hawaii, 10am!

785
00:57:21,560 --> 00:57:24,518
(cackles) I got you! A plane ticket!

786
00:57:24,600 --> 00:57:26,591
With my name on it.

787
00:57:26,680 --> 00:57:28,477
Oh, God!

788
00:57:28,560 --> 00:57:30,551
(knock at door)

789
00:57:34,840 --> 00:57:36,637
Cops!

790
00:57:37,560 --> 00:57:39,551
(knocking continues)

791
00:57:52,640 --> 00:57:54,631
Mr Lift?

792
00:57:57,800 --> 00:57:59,791
(heart thumping)

793
00:58:07,680 --> 00:58:09,750
We'd like to ask you a few questions.

794
00:58:09,840 --> 00:58:11,831
I hope there's no trouble.

795
00:58:11,920 --> 00:58:15,799
I was at the bowlin' alley all night.
I hope there's nothin' wrong.

796
00:58:16,040 --> 00:58:18,838
No, we'd like to ask you
about Professor Donner.

797
00:58:18,920 --> 00:58:22,117
- Professor Donner?
- Yes. Would you mind if we came in?

798
00:58:23,480 --> 00:58:25,948
- In the house?
- Just a few questions.

799
00:58:26,480 --> 00:58:28,994
I... I'm sorry. You can't.

800
00:58:31,360 --> 00:58:34,397
My momma's real sick.
I don't think it's a good idea.

801
00:58:34,800 --> 00:58:36,995
- It'll only take a minute.
- No, I...

802
00:58:42,280 --> 00:58:44,475
OK! All right. Come on up.

803
00:58:44,560 --> 00:58:47,552
If it'll only take a minute,
that won't be so bad.

804
00:58:48,080 --> 00:58:50,071
Would you like to meet my momma?

805
00:58:53,280 --> 00:58:57,592
We understand you take Professor
Donner's course at Valley College.

806
00:58:57,680 --> 00:58:59,910
Yeah. Creative writing.

807
00:59:00,000 --> 00:59:02,594
I'm gonna put my bowlin' ball away.

808
00:59:02,680 --> 00:59:06,673
- I'm his star pupil.
- Do you have any idea where he is?

809
00:59:06,760 --> 00:59:11,038
Did you try his apartment? He goes there
a lot. He keeps his stuff there.

810
00:59:12,960 --> 00:59:14,951
You guys wanna have some tea?

811
00:59:15,040 --> 00:59:17,031
We've got orange pekoe,...

812
00:59:17,120 --> 00:59:19,475
.. we've got Irish breakfast,...

813
00:59:19,560 --> 00:59:21,471
.. we've got Darjeeling...

814
00:59:21,560 --> 00:59:25,030
Mr Lift, have you ever heard
Professor Donner talk about his wife?

815
00:59:25,120 --> 00:59:29,671
Professor Donner? Oh, he... he always
talked about her like she was an angel.

816
00:59:29,760 --> 00:59:32,991
He loved his wife.
He worshipped the ground she... Hi.

817
00:59:35,000 --> 00:59:37,673
Hi, tea! Hi, tea. Hi.

818
00:59:37,760 --> 00:59:41,070
You never heard him say
anything bad about her?

819
00:59:42,080 --> 00:59:46,073
Oh. This is Irish breakfast.
I'll get Darjeeling.

820
00:59:46,160 --> 00:59:49,391
Whatever you want, Mr Lift.
We won't be havin' any.

821
00:59:50,720 --> 00:59:53,393
- What was that question again?
- (Momma) Owen!

822
00:59:56,160 --> 00:59:58,435
Momma! You're alive!

823
01:00:00,560 --> 01:00:02,835
Old people - you have to reassure them.

824
01:00:04,840 --> 01:00:07,513
Mr Lift, can we get back
to Professor Donner?

825
01:00:07,920 --> 01:00:11,913
Yes. By all means, let's get back to him.

826
01:00:13,240 --> 01:00:16,152
- Mr Lift...
- Oh! You know what?

827
01:00:16,240 --> 01:00:18,595
This... This box is empty.

828
01:00:18,680 --> 01:00:21,717
Could you get me some tea in the pantry?

829
01:00:22,360 --> 01:00:24,954
Sure. No problem.

830
01:00:26,560 --> 01:00:30,792
(detective) You said that he loved his wife.
What gave you that idea?

831
01:00:31,760 --> 01:00:33,751
Oh! I'm sorry, officer.

832
01:00:33,840 --> 01:00:37,594
I have some tea right here on the stove.
It won't be necessary.

833
01:00:37,680 --> 01:00:40,990
- Oh. No problem.
- What was that question again?

834
01:00:41,080 --> 01:00:43,719
What makes you think
that he loved his wife?

835
01:00:45,600 --> 01:00:48,398
But you know what you could get me
is some sugar.

836
01:00:48,480 --> 01:00:51,119
Is it in the pantry?

837
01:00:51,520 --> 01:00:53,715
- Yeah.
- No problem.

838
01:00:53,800 --> 01:00:58,555
I shouldn't use sugar in my tea because
I'm carryin' around this spare tyre.

839
01:00:58,640 --> 01:01:02,269
I'd like to get rid of it
but it's so hard to cut back.

840
01:01:03,080 --> 01:01:06,868
- Owen! You did it, didn't you, Owen?
- No, Momma, I didn't.

841
01:01:06,960 --> 01:01:10,270
- Yes, you did!
- No! Honest to God, I didn't do it!

842
01:01:10,360 --> 01:01:13,193
You told them to take me away!

843
01:01:13,280 --> 01:01:16,158
Oh. No, Momma. No.

844
01:01:16,240 --> 01:01:21,314
- You came to take me away!
- I'm sorry. My momma's not feelin' well.

845
01:01:21,400 --> 01:01:23,630
Not feeling well, my foot!

846
01:01:23,720 --> 01:01:25,551
- I'm sorry.
- You little bastard!

847
01:01:25,640 --> 01:01:28,200
I said you'd desert me, and you did!

848
01:01:28,280 --> 01:01:31,431
The only way they'll get me
outta here is to drag me out!

849
01:01:31,520 --> 01:01:34,512
You're gonna have to
take me out in a pine box!

850
01:01:35,840 --> 01:01:38,752
Get out! Get outta my house!

851
01:01:40,280 --> 01:01:42,077
Owen!

852
01:01:42,840 --> 01:01:44,831
You're grounded!

853
01:01:46,480 --> 01:01:49,074
I can't believe that you brought them here!

854
01:01:49,160 --> 01:01:51,879
- Why didn't you kill Momma?
- Because I'm not a killer!

855
01:01:51,960 --> 01:01:55,748
I can't put a pillow over her face
and squeeze the life out of her!

856
01:01:59,520 --> 01:02:02,353
- You see that door with the hook on it?
- Yeah.

857
01:02:02,440 --> 01:02:07,878
Every night around nine o'clock, she yells
"Bath" and hangs her shawl on that hook.

858
01:02:07,960 --> 01:02:10,315
- I'll bet that's where I come in.
- Yeah.

859
01:02:10,400 --> 01:02:12,550
- Now, how did I know that?
- Come on, come on.

860
01:02:12,640 --> 01:02:14,312
- Watch out for my skates.
- Ow!

861
01:02:20,160 --> 01:02:22,151
(hinge falls down stairs)

862
01:02:23,640 --> 01:02:26,552
She'll get out of her chair,
she'll go to the door,...

863
01:02:26,640 --> 01:02:30,155
.. you go behind her and pow!
Down the stairs she goes.

864
01:02:30,400 --> 01:02:33,870
- And where are you gonna be?
- Howie's Lanes. Come on.

865
01:02:46,920 --> 01:02:49,593
To hell with this guy! What am I? Crazy?

866
01:02:50,360 --> 01:02:52,635
I'm outta here. I can't stay here.

867
01:02:53,360 --> 01:02:55,874
- I can't stay in this house!
- (siren)

868
01:03:04,160 --> 01:03:06,151
Stand back, please.

869
01:03:18,040 --> 01:03:20,429
Milk and Mallomars...

870
01:03:44,000 --> 01:03:45,991
Bath!

871
01:03:47,160 --> 01:03:49,913
- Who the hell are you?!
- I'm Owen's friend.

872
01:03:50,000 --> 01:03:54,073
- Owen doesn't have a friend!
- That's because he's shy.

873
01:03:54,160 --> 01:03:56,196
No, he's not. He's fat and he's stupid.

874
01:03:56,280 --> 01:03:58,669
Get outta my house! Where is Owen?

875
01:03:58,760 --> 01:04:00,990
- Owen went bowling.
- I want Owen!

876
01:04:01,080 --> 01:04:03,753
- He'll be back soon.
- I want my bath and my medicine!

877
01:04:03,840 --> 01:04:06,229
- I can get it for you.
- Who the hell are you?

878
01:04:06,320 --> 01:04:08,356
- Let me hang that up.
- I can do it myself!

879
01:04:08,440 --> 01:04:12,752
- I know, but I'd like to hang it up for you.
- Get out of my way, you black bastard!

880
01:04:12,840 --> 01:04:14,478
What?!

881
01:04:14,640 --> 01:04:16,358
Mrs Lift!

882
01:04:16,440 --> 01:04:18,795
- He tried to kill me.
- What?

883
01:04:18,880 --> 01:04:21,235
I said, he's tryin' to kill me!

884
01:04:21,320 --> 01:04:22,833
Mrs Lift! Don't...

885
01:04:23,240 --> 01:04:25,629
I can hang up my own goddamn shawl.

886
01:04:28,800 --> 01:04:31,917
He's trying to kill me!

887
01:04:32,000 --> 01:04:36,118
I asked for the salted nuts!
He brought me the unsalted nuts!

888
01:04:36,200 --> 01:04:38,714
The unsalted nuts make me choke!

889
01:04:43,680 --> 01:04:45,557
Aargh!

890
01:04:56,280 --> 01:04:58,271
Pain in the ass!

891
01:05:04,080 --> 01:05:05,877
Oh, no!

892
01:05:19,320 --> 01:05:21,629
Your friend had an accident. He's dead!

893
01:05:21,720 --> 01:05:24,712
You go bowling and leave
a corpse to take care of me!

894
01:05:24,800 --> 01:05:27,394
- He's dead?
- See for yourself!

895
01:05:29,160 --> 01:05:31,151
Larry! My friend!

896
01:05:31,240 --> 01:05:34,835
- My friend! Larry!
- (mimics) "My friend! My friend!"

897
01:05:34,920 --> 01:05:36,911
You little crybaby!

898
01:05:37,000 --> 01:05:40,390
Go bury him in the yard
before he stinks up the place!

899
01:06:45,800 --> 01:06:47,677
Larry, you're alive!

900
01:06:50,640 --> 01:06:52,517
You killed her.

901
01:07:03,720 --> 01:07:07,235
Holy shit! What a dream I was having!

902
01:07:07,320 --> 01:07:09,550
Louis Armstrong was trying to kill me!

903
01:07:09,880 --> 01:07:13,190
- Mrs Lift?
- Get away from me, you horse's ass!

904
01:07:16,960 --> 01:07:18,951
(groans)

905
01:07:23,680 --> 01:07:27,070
She's not a woman. She's the Terminator.

906
01:07:32,080 --> 01:07:34,071
(dinging)

907
01:07:55,160 --> 01:07:58,197
The ex-husband of missing novelist
Margaret Donner...

908
01:07:58,280 --> 01:08:01,352
.. is wanted for questioning
but has now himself disappeared.

909
01:08:01,440 --> 01:08:06,116
If you have any information regarding his
whereabouts, contact your local police.

910
01:08:06,200 --> 01:08:09,476
Owen! There's a murderer in the house!

911
01:08:09,760 --> 01:08:12,274
Hello, police? I found him!
The wife murderer!

912
01:08:12,360 --> 01:08:14,555
- He's here!
- Gimme the phone!

913
01:08:14,960 --> 01:08:16,951
I'm on the next train to Mexico.

914
01:08:17,040 --> 01:08:20,635
- No! This is no time to panic.
- This is the perfect time to panic!

915
01:08:20,720 --> 01:08:24,838
She turned me in! Do what you want
with her. I gotta think about myself.

916
01:08:24,920 --> 01:08:26,911
Larry, don't leave me!

917
01:08:27,960 --> 01:08:29,598
Larry!

918
01:08:37,360 --> 01:08:39,157
(cracking)

919
01:08:46,320 --> 01:08:48,515
I'm sorry, Larry.

920
01:08:49,040 --> 01:08:50,837
It's OK, Owen.

921
01:08:51,120 --> 01:08:54,908
- I messed everything up.
- Owen, it's gonna be OK.

922
01:08:55,200 --> 01:08:56,997
I ruined your life.

923
01:08:57,080 --> 01:09:00,675
Come on, Owen. Sometimes
things happen in life for a reason.

924
01:09:02,080 --> 01:09:06,153
No, really. Maybe I was meant to go to
Mexico to be a writer. You never know.

925
01:09:06,520 --> 01:09:08,636
This is a great ending.

926
01:09:08,720 --> 01:09:12,235
I don't have the beginning,
but this is a great ending.

927
01:09:12,320 --> 01:09:15,915
Story of my life. I always have
great endings and no beginnings.

928
01:09:16,000 --> 01:09:18,514
That's not good for a writer, is it?

929
01:09:18,600 --> 01:09:20,591
No, it's not.

930
01:09:22,920 --> 01:09:25,878
How about "The night was humid"?

931
01:09:28,880 --> 01:09:31,633
- It's hot in here.
- Yeah, hot and close.

932
01:09:32,160 --> 01:09:35,311
- Moist.
- Right. "The night was moist. "

933
01:09:35,400 --> 01:09:39,029
This is what I'm talking about.
It's writing. Finding the perfect word.

934
01:09:39,120 --> 01:09:42,795
The perfect start. "It was the best
of times, it was the worst of times".

935
01:09:42,880 --> 01:09:44,871
"Now is the winter of our discontent".

936
01:09:44,960 --> 01:09:48,430
See what I'm saying?
Perfect beginnings. Perfect words.

937
01:09:48,520 --> 01:09:51,796
It's like us. We're on a train
to Mexico. We're on the lam.

938
01:09:51,880 --> 01:09:54,269
It's exciting, it's kinda mysterious.

939
01:09:54,360 --> 01:09:58,478
Do you say "The night was humid"
or "The night was moist"? That's writing!

940
01:09:58,560 --> 01:10:00,630
The night was sultry.

