it's "Margaret this" and "Margaret that".

999
01:14:07,680 --> 01:14:09,477
I'm sorry. I just can't help it.

1000
01:14:09,560 --> 01:14:12,836
Hate's no good. I'm not
living here with you in hate.

1001
01:14:13,600 --> 01:14:17,593
Get rid of it altogether, Larry,
or I'm leaving you.

1002
01:14:54,400 --> 01:14:56,197
Oh!

1003
01:14:58,440 --> 01:15:00,396
Oh, Larry!

1004
01:15:12,000 --> 01:15:13,797
Argh!

1005
01:15:13,880 --> 01:15:15,871
(static on TV)

1006
01:15:25,920 --> 01:15:28,229
(gentle snoring)

1007
01:15:43,040 --> 01:15:45,031
His name was Owen...

1008
01:15:45,120 --> 01:15:48,112
.. and he wanted me to kill his mother.

1009
01:15:48,680 --> 01:15:50,875
When I asked him why,...

1010
01:15:50,960 --> 01:15:53,952
.. he said because he didn't like her.

1011
01:15:54,840 --> 01:15:57,035
When I asked him why me,...

1012
01:15:57,680 --> 01:16:00,672
.. he said it was my idea.

1013
01:16:04,880 --> 01:16:07,553
I was teaching college...

1014
01:16:27,160 --> 01:16:29,151
(continues typing)

1015
01:16:39,240 --> 01:16:41,231
(rings)

1016
01:16:42,480 --> 01:16:44,994
- Hello.
- Aloha.

1017
01:16:45,080 --> 01:16:47,469
- Owen! How are ya!
- I'm fine.

1018
01:16:47,560 --> 01:16:50,916
- Where are you?
- In Topanga Canyon. I just killed Beth.

1019
01:16:51,000 --> 01:16:53,992
- What?
- Nah, I'm kiddin'. Look out your window.

1020
01:16:54,080 --> 01:16:56,594
You little couch potato!

1021
01:16:57,760 --> 01:17:00,513
- Hi, Owen!
- Hi, Larry.

1022
01:17:01,120 --> 01:17:03,395
- Owen, come on up.
- OK.

1023
01:17:04,240 --> 01:17:07,676
- I missed you.
- I missed you, too. It's been a year.

1024
01:17:07,760 --> 01:17:10,558
- Wow. You look terrific.
- Thank you. So do you.

1025
01:17:10,640 --> 01:17:13,029
- Well, thanks. How's Momma?
- Dead.

1026
01:17:13,120 --> 01:17:15,953
- Oh, I'm sorry.
- Mm, well...

1027
01:17:16,040 --> 01:17:17,678
Did you, um...

1028
01:17:17,760 --> 01:17:19,352
No!

1029
01:17:19,440 --> 01:17:21,908
No. Natural causes.

1030
01:17:22,280 --> 01:17:24,919
- That's good.
- Yeah, well.

1031
01:17:25,000 --> 01:17:28,549
- I see you're writing.
- I started the day I got outta the hospital.

1032
01:17:28,640 --> 01:17:32,792
And I haven't stopped, Owen. I'm half a
paragraph away from finishing my book!

1033
01:17:32,880 --> 01:17:35,269
- That's great!
- Yeah, it's really somethin'.

1034
01:17:35,360 --> 01:17:37,874
Well, you know what they say.

1035
01:17:37,960 --> 01:17:41,077
(both) A writer writes... always.

1036
01:17:41,560 --> 01:17:43,551
Well, look. I won't keep you from it.

1037
01:17:43,640 --> 01:17:46,871
- I just came by to say hello and...
- You just got here!

1038
01:17:46,960 --> 01:17:51,272
Actually, I gotta catch a plane. I'm goin'
to New York because... I wrote a book.

1039
01:17:51,360 --> 01:17:54,397
- What?
- It's gonna be on the stands in two days.

1040
01:17:54,840 --> 01:17:57,593
You wrote a book?
And it's gonna be published?

1041
